List-Subscribe: <http://lists.nongnu.org/mailman/listinfo/axiom-developer>,
	<mailto:axiom-developer-request@nongnu.org?subject=subscribe>
X-List-Received-Date: Wed, 02 May 2007 15:54:37 -0000

Probably in a similar way as \begin{verbatim} ... \end{verbatim} or 
\verb do it. Otherwise I would say one can restrict chunk names to 
ordinary LaTeX text similar to what noweb provides. Note one can have

<<$e^{i\pi}=-1$>>=
  ...
@

as a chunk in noweb.

Ralf

